The paper deals with a spatial crowdsourcing problem that involves assigning workers to tasks based on their location and movement. This problem has implications for database systems (cs.DB) as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed approximation algorithms and cost-model-based index involve computational intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.CE). Finally, the problem of spatial crowdsourcing and worker movement can also be seen as a form of social computing (cs.SI).
